The natural selection process has been observed in "real time". There are many cases, some of which are listed below, that illustrate this process at work.

 - The [industrial melanism](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Industrial_melanism#Industrial_melanism) that the [peppered moth](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peppered_moth_evolution) species developed is a classic example of natural selection at work.

 - [Antibiotic resistance](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antibiotic_resistance) in bacteria to penicillin treatment.
